# Routing Protocol (React Router v7)

## Structure

```
src/router/
  index.tsx          # createBrowserRouter — assembly point only
  routes.ts          # Route name/path constants
  modules/
    base.routes.tsx  # Base routes (home, 404, ...)
    admin.routes.tsx # Domain-specific route modules (add here)
```

## Adding a Route

1. Create page: `src/pages/FooPage/FooPage.tsx` + `index.ts` (lazy export).
2. Add route path constant to `src/router/routes.ts`.
3. Add to `src/router/modules/base.routes.tsx` (or create new module).
4. Wrap lazy page element with `WithSuspense`.
5. Assemble in `src/router/index.tsx` if new module.

```typescript
// routes.ts — path constants (actual export: RoutesPath — keys Root, Login, Dashboard, DevPlayground, NotFound)
export const RoutesPath = {
    Root: '/',
    Foo: '/foo',
    NotFound: '*'
} as const;

// base.routes.tsx
import { FooPage } from '@/pages/FooPage';
import { WithSuspense } from '@/hocs/WithSuspense';

{ path: RoutesPath.Foo, element: WithSuspense(<FooPage />) }
```

## Page Pattern

```typescript
// FooPage.tsx — the component
export const FooPage: FunctionComponent = () => { ... };

// index.ts — lazy export (used in router)
import { lazy } from 'react';
export const FooPage = lazy(() => import('./FooPage'));
```

**Exception**: Entry route (e.g., `HomePage`) can be non-lazy if it needs to be the initial load target.

## Navigation

```typescript
// Programmatic navigation
import { useNavigate } from 'react-router-dom';
const navigate = useNavigate();
navigate(RoutesPath.Foo);

// Declarative
import { Link } from 'react-router-dom';
<Link to={RoutesPath.Foo}>Go to Foo</Link>
```

## Anti-Patterns (FORBIDDEN)

- ❌ Hardcoded path strings in `<Link to="/foo">` — use `RoutesPath.Foo`.
- ❌ Lazy pages without `WithSuspense` — causes blank screen on load.
- ❌ Route logic (guards, redirects) in components — belongs in route module.
- ❌ Adding routes directly to `index.tsx` — always use a module file.
